ces/p2p-gpu/phases/06-bootstrap-model.sh","additions":187,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/phases/07-model-optimize.sh","additions":21,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/phases/08-vastai-quirks.sh","additions":55,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/phases/09-services.sh","additions":251,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/phases/10-voice-stack.sh","additions":19,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/phases/11-access-layer.sh","additions":32,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/phases/12-summary.sh","additions":21,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/setup.sh","additions":192,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/subcommands/fix.sh","additions":68,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/subcommands/info.sh","additions":20,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/subcommands/resume.sh","additions":36,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/subcommands/status.sh","additions":70,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"resources/p2p-gpu/subcommands/teardown.sh","additions":44,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"}],"reviewDecision":"CHANGES_REQUESTED","reviewRequests":[],"reviews":[{"id":"PRR_kwDORMI4oM72b0FX","author":{"login":"Lightheartdevs"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"Appreciate the scope discipline — keeping the entire toolkit in `resources/p2p-gpu/` with no core modifications is the right call. The architecture (lib/phases/subcommands split) mirrors the main installer cleanly.\n\n**Blocking issues:**\n\n1. **Philosophy drift from CLAUDE.md.** The project's error-handling contract is explicit: *\"Never `|| true` or `2>/dev/null`. No silent swallowing.\"* The file header in `setup.sh` claims `# Design: aligned with DreamServer CLAUDE.md — Let It Crash > KISS > Pure Functions > SOLID` but the implementation uses `|| warn \"... (non-fatal)\"` ~20 times and `|| true` as a fallback. `warn`-and-continue *is* silent swallowing — it just logs first. Please either:\n   - Let these errors crash (the philosophy the header claims), or\n   - Remove the CLAUDE.md alignment claim from the header and justify the non-fatal pattern on a case-by-case basis.\n\n2. **`chmod a+rwX` as documented fallback.** World-writable is a correctness and security smell on a shared remote host. Vast.ai boxes are ephemeral but still multi-tenant on the physical hardware. Setgid + POSIX ACLs should be the only path; the `chmod a+rwX` fallback should fail hard rather than degrade.\n\n3. **`integration-smoke` CI failure.** Needs to go green before merge — even if it's a pre-existing flake, confirm it's unrelated to this PR.\n\n4. **New CI workflow (`.github/workflows/p2p-gpu.yml`, +182 lines)** adds maintenance surface for what's positioned as a resources-tier add-on. Consider whether this is justified for code that, by its location in `resources/`, isn't part of the supported install path. If yes, add a maintainer comment explaining why it warrants first-class CI.\n\n**Non-blocking observations:**\n\n- The `service-hints.yaml` + per-provider quirk handling is genuinely useful and I'd love to see this land.\n- 28 provider quirks is a lot to maintain — a way for the community to contribute new hints without PRs against core would help long-term.\n\nHappy to re-review once the philosophy/permissions issues are addressed. Thanks for the submission — this is a real gap in the project and the architecture is sound.","submittedAt":"2026-04-18T14:01:57Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[{"content":"HEART","users":{"totalCount":1}}],"state":"CHANGES_REQUESTED","commit":{"oid":"6043119c29a4d2b8fcc867050a62d5513454fbcf"}}],"statusCheckRollup":[{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:13:07Z","conclusion":"FAILURE","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175735/job/73103873327","name":"integration-smoke","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:30Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Test Linux"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:36Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175731/job/73103873427","name":"Basic Review","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:30Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Claude Code Review"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:56Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175739/job/73103873282","name":"frontend","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:29Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Dashboard"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:55Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175744/job/73103873287","name":"powershell-lint (ubuntu-latest)","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:29Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Lint PowerShell"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:34Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175810/job/73103873377","name":"linux-smoke","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:30Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Matrix Smoke"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:15:08Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175742/job/73103873335","name":"Lint and smoke test p2p-gpu","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:30Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"P2P GPU Checks"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:36Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24967175733/job/73103873318","name":"Lint Python with Ruff","startedAt":"2026-04-26T21:12:29Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Python Lint"